Project: AquaVision Smart Boat Photo Logger (SENSATE-X 2.0 | TU Dublin)

Project Context: This project is developed as part of the BIP26 SENSATE-X 2.0 Short Term Mobility Programme at TU Dublin.
The goal is to build an intelligent, energy-efficient autonomous water surface vehicle (boat) designed for environmental monitoring and coastal tracking.

The boat dynamically tracks its live coordinates, computes its total traveled distance,
and pushes this critical telemetry data instantly over the air via a mobile Wi-Fi hotspot.
A central MQTT broker handles the transmission, enabling a live web dashboard to display the boat's movement on an interactive map in real-time,
completely eliminating the need for manual card extractions.

